---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Insights — ostk" description="Architectural discoveries and session learnings from building the OS. Data-backed analysis and design decisions.">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>Insights</h1>
    <p class="lede">Architectural discoveries and data from the sessions that built ostk.</p>

    <div class="insights-grid">

      <a href="/insights/context-injection" class="insight-card featured">
        <span class="card-badge">Data</span>
        <h3>Context Injection: Why Agents Waste Turns</h3>
        <p>AI coding agents spend most of their budget on orientation — reading READMEs, listing directories. Front-loading project context changes what happens on the first turn. Measured across 26 models on needle-bench.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/insights/claude-code-source" class="insight-card">
        <span class="card-badge">Analysis</span>
        <h3>What the Claude Code Source Reveals</h3>
        <p>207 commands. 184 tools. Five architectural gaps: no audit trail, no coordination, no context economics, no trust model, no invisible infrastructure.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/insights/local-first" class="insight-card">
        <span class="card-badge">Data</span>
        <h3>Local-First: Open Models With Context</h3>
        <p>A 24B open-weight model running locally with context injection outperforms larger API models without context. 16GB VRAM, no API dependency.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/insights/model-switch-handoff" class="insight-card">
        <span class="card-badge">Architecture</span>
        <h3>Model Switching Across Vendors</h3>
        <p>A compact handoff preserves context across vendor boundaries. Claude → Gemini → DeepSeek → Claude with no context loss.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/insights/compounding" class="insight-card">
        <span class="card-badge">Method</span>
        <h3>Compounding: Dependency-Driven Sprints</h3>
        <p>Ship what unblocks the most first. 152 tests from compounding order vs 14 from random. 44% close rate vs 22%.</p>
      </a>

    </div>

    <section class="session-insights">
      <h2>Session learnings</h2>
      <p>Shorter observations from individual build sessions. These informed specific design decisions.</p>

      <div class="insight-list">
        <div class="insight-item">
          <strong>Tack emerged, wasn't designed.</strong> Communication cost dropped from ~200 tokens/op to ~10 tokens/op within one session. 20x compression through mutual adaptation.
        </div>
        <div class="insight-item">
          <strong>SMP architecture.</strong> Human = big core (slow, precise). LLM = little core (fast, approximate). OS = bus. Same instruction set, different clock speeds.
        </div>
        <div class="insight-item">
          <strong>Agentfile as CPU socket.</strong> Immutable at boot. FROM declares architecture. TOOL declares instruction set. LIMIT declares physical constraints. WORK declares affinity.
        </div>
        <div class="insight-item">
          <strong>Every write is compile.</strong> Boot files regenerate on every write, not on demand. The OS is always current. No stale state.
        </div>
        <div class="insight-item">
          <strong>Invisible infrastructure wins.</strong> Silent mode (OS + shim, agent unaware) performed at least as well as prompted mode. The invisibility is the feature.
        </div>
        <div class="insight-item">
          <strong>The OS installs from what already exists.</strong> A git repo already contains everything the OS needs. The commit log, issues, file history — <code>ostk init</code> reads and compiles it.
        </div>
        <div class="insight-item">
          <strong>Intent dynamic programming.</strong> Session 1: <code>:correct X</code> → 3 turns. Session 5: instant. Session 10: the mistake never happens. Each correction memoizes a subproblem.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .lede {
    font-size: var(--ostk-text-md);
    color: var(--ostk-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--ostk-space-8);
  }

  .insights-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(18rem, 1fr));
    gap: var(--ostk-space-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--ostk-space-12);
  }

  .insight-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--ostk-space-2);
    padding: var(--ostk-space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--ostk-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--ostk-radius-md);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color var(--ostk-duration-fast) var(--ostk-easing);
  }

  .insight-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--ostk-needle-dim);
  }

  .insight-card.featured {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    border-color: var(--ostk-needle-dim);
    background: var(--ostk-bg-raised);
  }

  .card-badge {
    font-family: var(--ostk-font-mono);
    font-size: var(--ostk-text-xs);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--ostk-tracking-wide);
    color: var(--ostk-needle);
  }

  .insight-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--ostk-text-base);
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ostk-text-primary);
  }

  .insight-card p {
    font-size: var(--ostk-text-sm);
    color: var(--ostk-text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: var(--ostk-leading-relaxed);
  }

  .session-insights h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .insight-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--ostk-space-4);
  }

  .insight-item {
    padding: var(--ostk-space-4);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--ostk-border-subtle);
    font-size: var(--ostk-text-sm);
    color: var(--ostk-text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--ostk-leading-relaxed);
  }

  .insight-item strong {
    color: var(--ostk-text-primary);
  }
</style>
